{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"In this rather long sort of marathon presentation,"},{"time":4000,"text":"I've tried to break it up into three parts:"},{"time":6000,"text":"the first being a whole lot of examples on how it can be"},{"time":11000,"text":"a little bit more pleasurable to deal with a computer"},{"time":15000,"text":"and really address the qualities of the human interface."},{"time":18000,"text":"And these will be some simple design qualities"},{"time":21000,"text":"and they will also be some qualities of, if you will,"},{"time":24000,"text":"the intelligence of interaction."},{"time":26000,"text":"Then the second part will really just be examples of new technologies --"},{"time":30000,"text":"new media falling very much into that mold."},{"time":34000,"text":"Again, I will go through them as fast as possible."},{"time":37000,"text":"And then the last one will be some examples"},{"time":40000,"text":"I've been able to collect, which I think"},{"time":44000,"text":"illustrate this at least as best I can, in the world of entertainment."},{"time":50000,"text":"People have this belief -- and I share most of it --"},{"time":56000,"text":"that we will be using the TV screens or their equivalents"},{"time":60000,"text":"for electronic books of the future. But then you think,"},{"time":63000,"text":"\"My God! What a terrible image you get when you look at still pictures on TV.\""},{"time":68000,"text":"Well, it doesn't have to be terrible."},{"time":70000,"text":"And that is a slide taken from a TV set"},{"time":74000,"text":"and it was pre-processed to be very sympathetic to the TV medium,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and it absolutely looks beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"Well, what's happened? How did people get into this mess?"},{"time":87000,"text":"Where you are now, all of a sudden,"},{"time":89000,"text":"sitting in front of personal computers"},{"time":91000,"text":"and video text -- teletext systems,"},{"time":95000,"text":"and somewhat horrified by what you see on the screen?"},{"time":98000,"text":"Well, you have to remember that TV was designed"},{"time":101000,"text":"to be looked at eight times the distance of the diagonal."},{"time":104000,"text":"So you get a 13-inch, 19-inch, whatever, TV,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and then you should multiply that by eight"},{"time":111000,"text":"and that's the distance you should sit away from the TV set."},{"time":114000,"text":"Now we've put people 18 inches in front of a TV,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and all the artifacts that none of the original designers expected to be seen,"},{"time":124000,"text":"all of a sudden, are staring you in the face:"},{"time":126000,"text":"the shadow mask, the scan lines, all of that."},{"time":129000,"text":"And they can be treated very easily;"},{"time":131000,"text":"there are actually ways of getting rid of them,"},{"time":134000,"text":"there are actually ways of just making absolutely beautiful pictures."},{"time":140000,"text":"I'm talking here a little bit about display technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"Let me talk about how you might input information."},{"time":146000,"text":"And my favorite example is always fingers."},{"time":150000,"text":"I'm very interested in touch-sensitive displays."},{"time":152000,"text":"High-tech, high-touch. Isn't that what some of you said?"},{"time":156000,"text":"It's certainly a very important medium for input,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and a lot of people think that fingers are a very low-resolution"},{"time":166000,"text":"sort of stylus for inputting to a display."},{"time":170000,"text":"In fact, they're not: it's really a very, very high-resolution input medium --"},{"time":174000,"text":"you have to just do it twice, you have to touch the screen"},{"time":177000,"text":"and then rotate your finger slightly --"},{"time":180000,"text":"and you can move a cursor with great accuracy."},{"time":183000,"text":"And so when you see on the market these systems"},{"time":185000,"text":"that have just a few light emitting diodes on the side and are very low resolution,"},{"time":190000,"text":"it's nice that they exist because it still is better than nothing."},{"time":194000,"text":"But it, in some sense, misses the point:"},{"time":196000,"text":"namely, that fingers are a very, very high-resolution input medium."},{"time":202000,"text":"Now, what are some of the other advantages?"},{"time":204000,"text":"Well, the one advantage is that you don't have to pick them up,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and people don't realize how important that is --"},{"time":212000,"text":"not having to pick up your fingers to use them. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"When you think for a second of the mouse on Macintosh --"},{"time":222000,"text":"and I will not criticize the mouse too much --"},{"time":226000,"text":"when you're typing -- what you have -- you want to now put something --"},{"time":230000,"text":"first of all, you've got to find the mouse."},{"time":232000,"text":"You have to probably stop. Maybe not come to a grinding halt,"},{"time":237000,"text":"but you've got to sort of find that mouse. Then you find the mouse,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and you're going to have to wiggle it a little bit"},{"time":242000,"text":"to see where the cursor is on the screen."},{"time":244000,"text":"And then when you finally see where it is,"},{"time":246000,"text":"then you've got to move it to get the cursor over there,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and then -- \"Bang\" -- you've got to hit a button or do whatever."},{"time":251000,"text":"That's four separate steps versus typing and then touching"},{"time":254000,"text":"and typing and just doing it all in one motion --"},{"time":259000,"text":"or one-and-a-half, depending on how you want to count."},{"time":263000,"text":"Again, what I'm trying to do is just illustrate"},{"time":265000,"text":"the kinds of problems that I think face the designers"},{"time":269000,"text":"of new computer systems and entertainment systems"},{"time":272000,"text":"and educational systems"},{"time":275000,"text":"from the perspective of the quality of that interface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"And another advantage, of course, of using fingers is you have 10 of them."},{"time":283000,"text":"And we have never known how to do this technically,"},{"time":286000,"text":"so this slide is a fake slide."},{"time":288000,"text":"We never succeeded in using ten fingers,"},{"time":291000,"text":"but there are certain things you can do, obviously,"},{"time":294000,"text":"with more than one-finger input, which is rather fascinating."},{"time":299000,"text":"What we did stumble across was something ..."},{"time":302000,"text":"Again, which is typical of the computer field,"},{"time":305000,"text":"is when you have a bug that you can't get rid of you turn it into a feature."},{"time":310000,"text":"And maybe ... (Laughter)"},{"time":312000,"text":"maybe a mouse is a new kind of bug."},{"time":316000,"text":"But the bug in our case was in touch-sensitive displays:"},{"time":320000,"text":"we wanted to be able to draw -- you know, rub your finger"},{"time":324000,"text":"across the screen to input continuous points --"},{"time":327000,"text":"and there was just too much friction"},{"time":329000,"text":"created between your finger and the glass --"},{"time":331000,"text":"if glass was the substrate, which it usually is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"So we found that that actually was a feature"},{"time":338000,"text":"in the sense you could build a pressure-sensitive display."},{"time":341000,"text":"And when you touch it with your finger,"},{"time":343000,"text":"you can actually, then, introduce all the forces on the face of that screen,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and that actually has a certain amount of value."},{"time":352000,"text":"Let me see if I can load another disc"},{"time":354000,"text":"and show you, quickly, an example."},{"time":363000,"text":"Now, imagine a screen, which is not only touch-sensitive now,"},{"time":366000,"text":"it's pressure-sensitive."},{"time":368000,"text":"And it's pressure-sensitive to the forces both in the plane of the screen --"},{"time":372000,"text":"X, Y, and Z at least in one direction;"},{"time":374000,"text":"we couldn't figure out how to come in the other direction."},{"time":378000,"text":"But let me get rid of the slide,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and let's see if this comes on."},{"time":389000,"text":"OK. So there is the pressure-sensitive display in operation."},{"time":393000,"text":"The person's just, if you will, pushing on the screen to make a curve."},{"time":398000,"text":"But this is the interesting part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400000,"text":"I want to stop it for a second"},{"time":404000,"text":"because the movie is very badly made."},{"time":408000,"text":"And the particular display was built about six years ago,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and when we moved from one room to another room,"},{"time":413000,"text":"a rather large person sat on it and it got destroyed."},{"time":417000,"text":"So all we have is this record. (Laughter)"},{"time":420000,"text":"But imagine that screen having lots of objects on it"},{"time":428000,"text":"and the person has touched an object --"},{"time":431000,"text":"one of N -- like he did there, and then pushed on it."},{"time":436000,"text":"Now, imagine a program"},{"time":438000,"text":"where some of those objects are physically heavy and some are light:"},{"time":442000,"text":"one is an anvil on a fuzzy rug"},{"time":446000,"text":"and the other one is a ping-pong ball on a sheet of glass."},{"time":450000,"text":"And when you touch it, you have to really push very hard"},{"time":454000,"text":"to move that anvil across the screen,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and yet you touch the ping-pong ball very lightly"},{"time":459000,"text":"and it just scoots across the screen."},{"time":461000,"text":"And what you can do -- oops, I didn't mean to do that --"},{"time":466000,"text":"what you can do is actually feed back to the user"},{"time":470000,"text":"the feeling of the physical properties."},{"time":473000,"text":"So again, they don't have to be weight;"},{"time":476000,"text":"they could be a general trying to move troops,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and he's got to move an aircraft carrier versus a little boat."},{"time":483000,"text":"In fact, they funded it for that very reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"The whole notion, then, is one that at the interface"},{"time":496000,"text":"there are physical properties in that transducer --"},{"time":500000,"text":"in this case it's pressure and touches --"},{"time":502000,"text":"that allow you to present things to the user that you could never present before."},{"time":506000,"text":"So it's not simply looking at the quality or, if you will, the luxury of that interface,"},{"time":511000,"text":"but it's actually looking at the idea"},{"time":513000,"text":"of presenting things that previously couldn't be presented before."},{"time":516000,"text":"I want to move on to another example,"},{"time":520000,"text":"which is one of a different sort, where we're trying to use computer"},{"time":526000,"text":"and video disc technology now to come up with a new kind of book."},{"time":531000,"text":"Here, the idea is that you're going to take this book,"},{"time":536000,"text":"if you will, and it's going to come alive."},{"time":538000,"text":"You're going to sort of breathe life into it."},{"time":541000,"text":"We are so used to doing monologues."},{"time":545000,"text":"Filmmakers, for example, are the experts in monologue making:"},{"time":549000,"text":"you make a film and it has a well-formed beginning, middle and end,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and in some sense the art of it is that."},{"time":555000,"text":"And you then say, \"There's an opportunity"},{"time":559000,"text":"for making conversational movies.\" Well, what does that mean?"},{"time":563000,"text":"And it sort of nibbles at the core of the whole profession"},{"time":569000,"text":"and all the assumptions of that medium."},{"time":571000,"text":"So, book writing is the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"What I'll show you very quickly is a new kind of book"},{"time":577000,"text":"where it is mixed now with ... all sorts of things live in there,"},{"time":581000,"text":"but you have to keep a few things in mind."},{"time":584000,"text":"One is that this book knows about itself."},{"time":589000,"text":"Each frame of the movie has information about itself."},{"time":595000,"text":"So it knows, or at least there is computer-readable information"},{"time":600000,"text":"in the medium itself. It's just not a static movie frame."},{"time":604000,"text":"That's one thing. The other is that you have to realize"},{"time":606000,"text":"that it is a random access medium,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and you can, in fact, branch and expand and elaborate and shrink."},{"time":612000,"text":"And here -- again, my favorite example -- is the cookbook,"},{"time":616000,"text":"the \"Larousse Gastronomique.\""},{"time":619000,"text":"And I think I use the example all too often,"},{"time":622000,"text":"but it's a great one because there is a classic ending in that little"},{"time":627000,"text":"encyclopedia-style cookbook that tells you how to do something like penguin,"},{"time":634000,"text":"and you get to the end of the recipe and it says, \"Cook until done.\""},{"time":638000,"text":"Now, that would be, if you will, the top green track,"},{"time":643000,"text":"which doesn't mean too much. But you might have to elaborate for me"},{"time":647000,"text":"or for somebody who isn't an expert, and say,"},{"time":649000,"text":"\"Cook at 380 degrees for 45 minutes.\""},{"time":651000,"text":"And then for a real beginner, you would go down even further"},{"time":654000,"text":"and elaborate more -- say, \"Open the oven, preheat, wait for the light to go out,"},{"time":658000,"text":"open the door, don't leave it open too long,"},{"time":661000,"text":"put the penguin in and shut the door ...\" (Laughter) whatever."},{"time":664000,"text":"And that's a much more elaborate one than you dribble back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667000,"text":"That's one kind of use of random access."},{"time":672000,"text":"And the other is where you want to explain the same thing in different ways."},{"time":680000,"text":"If you're in a classroom situation and somebody asks a question,"},{"time":684000,"text":"the last thing you do is repeat what you just said."},{"time":687000,"text":"You try and think of a different way of saying the same thing,"},{"time":691000,"text":"or if you know the particular student and that student's cognitive style,"},{"time":696000,"text":"then you might say it in a way that you think"},{"time":698000,"text":"would have a good impedance match with that student."},{"time":701000,"text":"There are all sorts of techniques you will use --"},{"time":703000,"text":"and again, this is a different kind of branching."},{"time":707000,"text":"So, what I will show you is ... it's a rather boring book,"},{"time":713000,"text":"but I'm afraid sometimes you have to do boring books"},{"time":716000,"text":"because your sponsors aren't necessarily interested in fiction"},{"time":721000,"text":"and entertainment. And this is a book on how to repair a transmission."},{"time":727000,"text":"Now, I don't even know what vintage the transmission is,"},{"time":730000,"text":"but let me just show you very quickly some of it, and we'll move on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: And continue to get descriptions for each of these chapters."},{"time":744000,"text":"Nicholas Negroponte: Now, this is his table of contents."},{"time":746000,"text":"Just a picture of the transmission, and as you rub your finger across the transmission"},{"time":750000,"text":"it highlights the various parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"Narrator: When I find a chapter that I want to see,"},{"time":755000,"text":"I just touch the text and the system will format pages for me to read."},{"time":767000,"text":"The words or phrases that are lit up in red are glossary words,"},{"time":773000,"text":"so I can get a different definition by just touching the word,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and the definition appears, superimposed over the illustration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"NN: This is about the oil pan, or the oil filter and all that."},{"time":812000,"text":"This is relatively important because it sets the page ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"Narrator: This is another example of a page with glossary words"},{"time":821000,"text":"highlighted in red."},{"time":825000,"text":"I can get a definition of these words just by touching them,"},{"time":828000,"text":"and the definition will appear in the illustration corner."},{"time":836000,"text":"I can get back to the illustration, but in this case it's not a single frame,"},{"time":841000,"text":"but it's actually a movie of someone coming into the frame and doing the repair"},{"time":844000,"text":"that's described in the text."},{"time":847000,"text":"The two-headed slider is a speed control that allows me to watch the movie"},{"time":851000,"text":"at various speeds, in forward or reverse."},{"time":854000,"text":"And the movie is displayed as a full frame movie."},{"time":859000,"text":"I can go back to the beginning ... and play the movie at full speed."},{"time":877000,"text":"Here's another step-by-step procedure, only in this case --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"NN: Okay, this movie is ... Everybody's heard of sound-sync movies --"},{"time":883000,"text":"this is text-sync movies, so as the movie plays, the text gets highlighted."},{"time":888000,"text":"We highlight the text as we go through the movie."},{"time":892000,"text":"Repairman: ... Not too far out. Front poles, preferably."},{"time":896000,"text":"Don't loosen them too far. If you loosen them too far, you'll have a big mess."},{"time":902000,"text":"NN: I suspect that some of you might not even understand that language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":911000,"text":"OK. I'm at the third and last part of this,"},{"time":916000,"text":"which I said I would make an attempt to at least give you some examples"},{"time":920000,"text":"that may be more directly related to the world of entertainment."},{"time":924000,"text":"And of course, good education has got to be good entertainment,"},{"time":929000,"text":"so my first example will be drawn from a very recent experiment"},{"time":936000,"text":"that we've been doing -- in this case, in Senegal --"},{"time":939000,"text":"where we have tried to use personal computers"},{"time":944000,"text":"as a pedagogical medium. But not as teaching machines at all;"},{"time":949000,"text":"the whole notion is to use this as an instrument"},{"time":953000,"text":"where there is a complete reversal of roles --"},{"time":956000,"text":"the child is, if you will, the teacher and the machine is the student --"},{"time":960000,"text":"and the art of computer programming is a vehicle that sort of"},{"time":962000,"text":"approximates thinking about thinking."},{"time":965000,"text":"But teaching kids programming per se is utterly irrelevant."},{"time":970000,"text":"And there are just a few slides I want to go through,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":973000,"text":"but there's a story I'd like to tell. And that was when,"},{"time":979000,"text":"before we did this in any developing countries --"},{"time":981000,"text":"we're doing it, in fact, in three developing countries right now:"},{"time":983000,"text":"Pakistan, Colombia and Senegal --"},{"time":985000,"text":"we did it in some pretty rough areas of New York City."},{"time":990000,"text":"And one child, whose name I've forgotten, was about seven or eight years old,"},{"time":995000,"text":"absolutely considered mentally handicapped --"},{"time":1000000,"text":"couldn't read, didn't even make it in the lowest section of the school's classes --"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and was pretty much not in school, though physically there."},{"time":1011000,"text":"But did hang around the, quote, \"computer room,\""},{"time":1014000,"text":"where there were quite a few computers,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and learned this particular language called Logo --"},{"time":1020000,"text":"and learned it with great ease and found it a lot of fun,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"it was very interesting. And one day, by chance,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"some visitors from the NIE came by in their double-breasted suits"},{"time":1034000,"text":"looking at this setup, and none of the children who were normally there,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"except for this one child, were there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"He was, and he said, \"Let me show you how this works,\""},{"time":1046000,"text":"and they got an absolutely ingenuous, wonderful description of Logo."},{"time":1051000,"text":"And the child was just zipping right through it, showing them all sorts of things"},{"time":1055000,"text":"until they asked him how to do something which he couldn't explain"},{"time":1059000,"text":"and so he flipped through the manual, found the explanation"},{"time":1062000,"text":"and typed the command and got it to do what they asked."},{"time":1064000,"text":"They were delighted, and by the time it was time to go see the principal,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"whom they'd actually come to see -- not the computer room --"},{"time":1071000,"text":"they went upstairs and they said,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"\"This is absolutely remarkable!"},{"time":1074000,"text":"That child was very articulate and showed us"},{"time":1078000,"text":"and even dealt with the things he couldn't do automatically"},{"time":1082000,"text":"with that manual. It was just absolutely fantastic.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086000,"text":"The principal said, \"There's a dreadful mistake,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"because that child can't read."},{"time":1091000,"text":"And you obviously have been hoodwinked"},{"time":1093000,"text":"or you've talked about somebody else.\""},{"time":1096000,"text":"And they all got up and they all went downstairs"},{"time":1098000,"text":"and the child was still there. And they did something very intelligent:"},{"time":1102000,"text":"they asked the child, \"Can you read?\""},{"time":1106000,"text":"And the child said, \"No, I can't.\""},{"time":1109000,"text":"And then they said, \"But wait a minute. You"},{"time":1111000,"text":"just looked through that manual and you found ... \""},{"time":1114000,"text":"and he said, \"Oh, but that's not reading.\""},{"time":1117000,"text":"And so they said, \"Well, what's reading then?\""},{"time":1119000,"text":"He says, \"Well, reading is this junk they give me in little books to read."},{"time":1123000,"text":"It's absolutely irrelevant, (Laughter) and I get nothing for it."},{"time":1130000,"text":"But here, with a little bit of effort I get a lot of return.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"And it really meant something to the child."},{"time":1136000,"text":"The child read beautifully, it turned out,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"and was really very competent. So it actually meant something."},{"time":1142000,"text":"And that story has many other anecdotes that are similar,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"but wow. The key to the future of computers in education is right there,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"and it is: when does it mean something to a child?"},{"time":1157000,"text":"There is a myth, and it truly is a myth:"},{"time":1160000,"text":"we believe -- and I'm sure a lot of you believe in this room --"},{"time":1163000,"text":"that it is harder to read and write than it is to learn how to speak."},{"time":1168000,"text":"And it's not, but we think speech -- \"My God, little children pick it up somehow,"},{"time":1174000,"text":"and by the age of two they're doing a mediocre job,"},{"time":1176000,"text":"and by three and four they're speaking reasonably well."},{"time":1179000,"text":"And yet you've got to go to school to learn how to read,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"and you have to sit in a classroom and somebody has to teach you."},{"time":1184000,"text":"Hence, it must be harder.\" Well, it's not harder."},{"time":1187000,"text":"What the truth is is that speaking has great value to a child;"},{"time":1194000,"text":"the child can get a great deal by talking to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1197000,"text":"Reading and writing is utterly useless."},{"time":1199000,"text":"There is no reason for a child to read and write except blind faith,"},{"time":1204000,"text":"and that it's going to help you. (Laughter)"},{"time":1207000,"text":"So what happens is you go to school and people say,"},{"time":1210000,"text":"\"Just believe me, you're going to like it."},{"time":1213000,"text":"You're going to like reading,\" and just read and read."},{"time":1216000,"text":"On the other hand, you give a kid -- a three-year-old kid -- a computer"},{"time":1220000,"text":"and they type a little command and -- Poof! -- something happens."},{"time":1223000,"text":"And all of a sudden ... You may not call that reading and writing,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"but a certain bit of typing and reading stuff on the screen"},{"time":1229000,"text":"has a huge payoff, and it's a lot of fun."},{"time":1232000,"text":"And in fact, it's a powerful educational instrument."},{"time":1236000,"text":"Well, in Senegal we found that this was the traditional classroom:"},{"time":1241000,"text":"120 kids -- three per desk -- one teacher, a little bit of chalk."},{"time":1246000,"text":"This student was one of our first students,"},{"time":1249000,"text":"and it's the girl on the left leaning with her chalkboard,"},{"time":1253000,"text":"and she came ... within two days --"},{"time":1256000,"text":"I want to show you the program she wrote,"},{"time":1258000,"text":"and remember her hairstyle. And that is the program she made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1264000,"text":"That's what meant something to her, is doing the hair pattern,"},{"time":1268000,"text":"and actually did it within two days -- an hour each day --"},{"time":1273000,"text":"and found it was, to her,"},{"time":1275000,"text":"absolutely the most meaningful piece ..."},{"time":1278000,"text":"But rooted in that, little did she know how much knowledge"},{"time":1282000,"text":"she was acquiring about geometry"},{"time":1284000,"text":"and just math and logic and all the rest."},{"time":1287000,"text":"And again, I could talk for three hours about this subject."},{"time":1290000,"text":"I will come to my last example and then quit."},{"time":1298000,"text":"And my last example -- as some of my former colleagues,"},{"time":1304000,"text":"whom I see in the room, can imagine what it will be."},{"time":1307000,"text":"Yes, it is. It's our work -- that was a while ago,"},{"time":1310000,"text":"and it still is my favorite project -- of teleconferencing."},{"time":1314000,"text":"And the reason it remains a favorite project"},{"time":1316000,"text":"is that we were asked to do a teleconferencing system"},{"time":1323000,"text":"where you had the following situation:"},{"time":1325000,"text":"you had five people at five different sites -- they were known people --"},{"time":1330000,"text":"and you had to have these people in teleconference,"},{"time":1335000,"text":"such that each one was utterly convinced"},{"time":1338000,"text":"that the other four were physically present."},{"time":1342000,"text":"Now, that is sufficiently"},{"time":1346000,"text":"zany that we would, obviously, jump to the bait, and we did."},{"time":1351000,"text":"And the fact that we knew the people --"},{"time":1354000,"text":"we had to take a page out of the history of Walt Disney --"},{"time":1357000,"text":"we actually went so far as to build CRTs"},{"time":1360000,"text":"in the shapes of the people's faces."},{"time":1363000,"text":"So if I wanted to call my friend Peter Sprague on the phone,"},{"time":1368000,"text":"my secretary would get his head out and bring it and set it on the desk,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1371000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1372000,"text":"and that would be the TV used for the occasion."},{"time":1377000,"text":"And it's uncanny: there's no way I can explain to you"},{"time":1380000,"text":"the amount of eye contact you get with that physical face"},{"time":1384000,"text":"projected on a 3D CRT of that sort."},{"time":1388000,"text":"The next thing that we had to do is to persuade them"},{"time":1391000,"text":"that there needed to be spatial correspondence, which is straightforward,"},{"time":1395000,"text":"but again, it's something that didn't fall naturally"},{"time":1397000,"text":"out of a telecommunications or computing style of thinking;"},{"time":1400000,"text":"it was a very, if you will, architectural or spatial concept."},{"time":1404000,"text":"And that was to recognize that when you sit around the table,"},{"time":1407000,"text":"the actual location of the people becomes rather important."},{"time":1412000,"text":"And when somebody gets up, in fact, to go answer a phone"},{"time":1415000,"text":"or use a bathroom or something, the empty seat becomes,"},{"time":1418000,"text":"if you will, that person. And you point frequently to the empty seat"},{"time":1421000,"text":"and you say, \"He or she wouldn't agree,\""},{"time":1424000,"text":"and the empty chair is that person and the spatiality is crucial."},{"time":1430000,"text":"So we said, \"Well, these will be on round tables"},{"time":1433000,"text":"and the order around the table had to be the same,"},{"time":1436000,"text":"so that at my site, I would be, if you will, real"},{"time":1439000,"text":"and then at each other's site you'd have these plastic heads."},{"time":1444000,"text":"And the plastic heads, sometimes you want to project them."},{"time":1448000,"text":"And there are a number of schemes, which I don't want to dwell on,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1451000,"text":"but this is the one that we finally used"},{"time":1453000,"text":"where we projected onto rear screen material"},{"time":1457000,"text":"that was molded in the face -- literally in the face of the person."},{"time":1461000,"text":"And I'll show you one more slide, where this is actually made"},{"time":1465000,"text":"from something called a solid photograph and is the screen."},{"time":1469000,"text":"Now, we track, on the person's head, the head motions --"},{"time":1472000,"text":"so we transmit with a video the head positions --"},{"time":1476000,"text":"and so this head moves in about two axes."},{"time":1483000,"text":"So if I, all of a sudden, turn to the person to my left"},{"time":1488000,"text":"and start talking to that person, then at the person to my right's site,"},{"time":1493000,"text":"he'll see these two plastic heads talking to each other."},{"time":1496000,"text":"And then if that person interrupts, then those two heads may turn."},{"time":1501000,"text":"And it really is reconstructing, quite accurately, teleconferencing."}]}]}